      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Good",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "4.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Well developed characters can make or break an RPG’s story and ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Rise of the Third Power’s",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " are the driving focus, each with individual goals and ideals which often result in party arguments and discussions. You see these characters progressively work through their flaws and become better people, such as a pampered recluse being thrusted into the world or a washed up former pirate finding their purpose in life. This extends to characters outside of the main party, making the world feel believable while constructing an immersive tale of a grand adventure.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The game’s 1930s European inspiration leading up to World War II cleverly lays the foundations of its plot while also including the two previous decades since the great war prior as influence behind the party’s actions. There is political intrigue, betrayal and an underdog story of rebellion that spans several nations. The writing team at Stegosoft have provided an excellent story whilst uniquely combining modern history with a mediaeval fantasy setting.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "html",
        "html": "<a href=\"https://powera.pxf.io/c/3324894/1309898/15385\" target=\"_top\" id=\"1309898\"><img src=\"//a.impactradius-go.com/display-ad/15385-1309898\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"728\" height=\"90\"/></a><img height=\"0\" width=\"0\" src=\"https://imp.pxf.io/i/3324894/1309898/15385\" style=\"position:absolute;visibility:hidden;\" border=\"0\" />"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The classic console RPG has two iconic aspects that identify them above others: solid turn-based mechanics and great music, and ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Rise of the Third Power",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " has both of these boxes ticked with a bold quill. The boss battle theme is absolutely banging, with the only caveat being too short, especially during some of the more lengthy boss battles.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Each party has their own specialisation in combat, with both single and multitarget attacks, tanking, debuffs and healing. At the start of each combat encounter, you can choose three party members to fight and throughout the battle, the player can swap out members individually three times throughout, with the newly added character being placed at the end of the action round. A lot of strategy goes into each encounter, especially during boss battles and elite enemy spawns.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
